aregiver contacts to your app, beyond the allotted number, may cost a few extra dollars a month. Knowing that everyone gets important information, or receives updates in an emergency may be worth the extra costs. \"]}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"7\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Accessories: \"}],\"Adding a lockbox (a locked box on the outside of your house with extra keys) so emergency responders can enter your house, additional necklaces, or more discreet device accessories, and other product add-ons often cost extra. Many brands offer deals like a free lockbox with an annual payment plan, so it’s worth looking for those promotions when purchasing a device. \"]}],\"\\n\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"$L8b\",\"250\",{\"codeName\":\"c863ab0d_b65f_01d7_3022_95cc102fde29\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h2\",\"252\",{\"id\":\"how-to-save-money-on-medical-alert-systems\",\"children\":\"How to save money on medical alert systems\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"254\",{\"children\":[\"Unfortunately, most \",[\"$\",\"$L7c\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"/article/does-insurance-cover-medical-alert-systems/\",\"children\":\"private insurance plans\"}],\" and traditional Medicare \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"3\",{\"href\":\"https://www.medicare.gov/what-medicare-covers/what-part-a-covers\",\"children\":\"Part A\"}],\" and \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"5\",{\"href\":\"https://www.medicare.gov/what-medicare-covers/what-part-b-covers\",\"children\":\"Part B\"}],\" don’t cover medical alert systems.\",[\"$\",\"strong\",\"7\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"sup\",null,{\"children\":\"9,10\"}]}],\" And the initial fees to set up your device and subscription fees to monitor your system can quickly add up. \"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"256\",{\"children\":\"Here are some ways you can save on a medical alert system:\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"ul\",\"258\",{\"children\":[\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"1\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Medicare Advantage: \"}],\"Also known as \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"2\",{\"href\":\"https://www.medicare.gov/sign-up-change-plans/types-of-medicare-health-plans/medicare-advantage-plans/how-do-medicare-advantage-plans-work\",\"children\":\"Medicare Part C\"}],\", some of these plans offer partial or full coverage for medical alert systems and their subscription fees.\",[\"$\",\"strong\",\"4\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"sup\",null,{\"children\":\"11\"}]}],\" Check with your insurance provider directly to learn about your coverage.\"]}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"3\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Prepaying subscription fees: \"}],\"Many medical alert system companies offer discounts for paying quarterly or annually. You may also receive a free lockbox or other incentives for paying your fees in advance. If you choose to save this way, double-check your plan’s cancellation policy and ensure you’ll receive any money you prepaid back if you cancel. \"]}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"5\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Using an HSA or FSA account:\"}],\" A health savings account (HSA) or flexible spending account (FSA) allows you to use pre-taxed money to help pay for approved medical expenses. These accounts are often available through an employer.\"]}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"7\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Sales and discounts:\"}],\" Medical alert system companies often offer discounts and sales, some seasonal, and other deals are available regularly, like a free month when you pay annually. \"]}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"9\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Membership discounts: \"}],\"Organizations like the Department of Veterans Affairs may offer discounts for those who qualify. You may also be able to find local discounts through your \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"2\",{\"href\":\"https://eldercare.acl.gov/Public/About/Aging_Network/AAA.aspx\",\"children\":\"area agency on aging\"}],\". \"]}],\"\\n\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h2\",\"260\",{\"id\":\"how-to-set-up-your-medical-alert-system\",\"children\":\"How to set up your medical alert system\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"262\",{\"children\":\"Our testers found setting up medical alert devices to be a quick and easy process. Most devices we tested included a quick setup guide with three to five steps to set up your device. \"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"264\",{\"children\":\"To set up an at-home device, you’ll need to:\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"ul\",\"266\",{\"children\":[\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"1\",{\"children\":\"Find an outlet in a central location, not connected to a wall switch\"}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"3\",{\"children\":\"Plug your base station into the outlet\"}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"5\",{\"children\":\"If your device uses a landline, plug the phone cord into your device and the phone jack\"}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"Make sure your device is turned on\"}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"9\",{\"children\":\"Follow any testing instructions provided by your system\"}],\"\\n\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"$L8b\",\"268\",{\"codeName\":\"n261f7821_b5f5_011c_f9f4_32f64926922d\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"270\",{\"children\":\"To set up a mobile device, you’ll need to:\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"ul\",\"272\",{\"children\":[\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"1\",{\"children\":\"Plug the device’s charging cradle into an outlet\"}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"3\",{\"children\":\"Fit the device into its charger and let it charge until ready to use (four hours, on average)\"}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"5\",{\"children\":\"Make sure your device is connected to the cellular network (most devices connect automatically)\"}],\"\\n  \",[\"$\",\"li\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"Once your device is fully charged and connected to cellular, follow any testing instructions your system provides.\"}],\"\\n\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"274\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Note: All medical alert system users need to test their devices regularly. \"}]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"$L8b\",\"276\",{\"codeName\":\"n5668d9c0_c0ac_0161_c5f1_4d010a655f6a\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"278\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"—\"}],[\"$\",\"a\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.healthgrades.com/physician/dr-stephen-yeh-3y5hl\",\"data-new-window\":\"true\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"em\",null,{\"children\":\"Stephen Yeh\"}]}],[\"$\",\"em\",\"2\",{\"children\":\", MD, a board-certified emergency physician in Charlotte, North Carolina\"}]]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h2\",\"280\",{\"id\":\"importance-of-medical-alert-systems\",\"children\":\"Importance of medical alert systems\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"282\",{\"children\":[\"The biggest benefit we’ve found among users of medical alert systems is increased quality of life. In a poll by the University of Michigan’s Institute for Healthcare Policy and Innovation, 88% of adults age 50–80 felt it was \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.healthyagingpoll.org/reports-more/report/older-adults-preparedness-age-place\",\"children\":\"important to remain in their homes\"}],\" for as long as possible.\",[\"$\",\"strong\",\"3\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"sup\",null,{\"children\":\"12\"}]}],\" Yet the same study found that only 15% had given a lot of consideration to modifications their home may need to age in place safely. \"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"284\",{\"children\":[\"Using a medical alert system can extend how long someone can remain safely in their home. In addition to providing medical care when needed, a 2017 study showed that those who use a medical alert system \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/01621424.2017.1373718#d1e1168\",\"children\":\"feel more safe and secure\"}],\" and are more active around their homes.\",[\"$\",\"strong\",\"3\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"sup\",null,{\"children\":\"13\"}]}],\" Feeling more confident in completing tasks and engaging with their community can benefit both physical and mental health. \"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h2\",\"286\",{\"id\":\"faq\",\"children\":\"FAQ\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h3\",\"288\",{\"children\":\"Does Medicare cover medical alert systems?\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"290\",{\"children\":\"Medicare Part A and Part B do not cover medical alert systems, though some Medicare Advantage plans may cover all or part of a system’s cost. To learn more about whether your Medicare plan covers a medical alert system, call your insurance provider.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h3\",\"292\",{\"children\":\"How much do medical alert systems cost?\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"294\",{\"children\":\"Medical alert systems typically charge a subscription fee of $20–$60 a month for 24/7 access to a professional monitoring center. Some system plans also charge a one-time setup or equipment fee that may cost as much as $200 or more.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h3\",\"296\",{\"children\":\"Are there medical alert systems without a monthly fee?\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"298\",{\"children\":\"Yes. Unmonitored medical alert systems don’t charge a monthly fee. Typically, these systems don’t offer professional monitoring. Instead, when a user presses the help button, they are connected directly to 911 or to pre-selected contacts.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h3\",\"300\",{\"children\":\"Do you need Wi-Fi for medical alert systems?\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"302\",{\"children\":\"No, Wi-Fi is not required for most medical alert systems. In-home systems usually connect through a landline or a built-in cellular network to link the base station with the monitoring center. Mobile or on-the-go systems use cellular service and GPS to track the user’s location and connect to monitoring staff.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"304\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Questions?\"}],\" Email us at \",[\"$\",\"$L7c\",\"2\",{\"href\":\"mailto:reviewsteam@ncoa.org\",\"children\":\"reviewsteam@ncoa.org\"}],\" \"]}]]}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"footer\",null,{\"className\":\"\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"footnotes_h